@yegor256 yes, the Manifest.MF is shipped with the jar, but at runtime the code looks in the ``.war``'s Manifest.MF, doesn't go down the dependency tree to look in the jar's manifest.mf (that's what it looks like, and they are certainly not merged, so the war's manifest.mf doesn't contain info from its jars manifests)

More precisely, the code looks in this Manifest.MF:

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6305156/20514714/31bfadc8-b096-11e6-893d-c501cd039481.png)

while the 3 attributes are found in this one:

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6305156/20514735/5c1cc61e-b096-11e6-8473-b8b21a050af1.png)



The point is, I had to hardcode the 3 attribtues in the ``.war``'s Manifest.MF, using maven's assembly plugin (see [here](https://github.com/opencharles/charles-github-ejb/blob/master/pom.xml#L30))- and others had this exact issue as well, see [here](https://github.com/jcabi/jcabi-github/issues/1198)
